ture hath not a word; yea the thing they most of all obiected agaynst our Sauiour, was the written Tradition of Moyses about keeping the Sabboth Day. [Ioan. 7.] From which precept not by Tradition vnwritten, but by Logicall inference, they concluded that our Lord brake the Sabboth-Day by healing diseased persons thereon. So that Pharasaicall Traditions were neuer so much as pretended to be doctrines vnwritten as you imagine, but to be doctrines concluded from the text of Scripture, by the rules of Reason and Logicke, iust according to your Protestant pretence.
